[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] Ethics Statement
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] The research protocol was reviewed by an ethics committee
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] at the University of Edinburgh’s School of Informatics. Par-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] ticipants were provided with a standard participant infor-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] mation sheet and consent form prior to each interview. Par-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] ticipants could consent to either audio or video recording,
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] and were informed that their participation was voluntary,
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] with the option to withdraw at any time. They were also
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] made aware of how their interview data would be stored and
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] retained for the duration of the study. All participant data
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] was anonymized at the point of transcription, with individ-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] ual participants assigned a random generated Participant ID
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] number. Furthermore, participant affiliations were kept con-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] fidential to avoid identifiability. Due to the aforementioned
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] steps, we do not foresee any risks for participants of this
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] study.
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] Researcher Positionality
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] The authors of this study are based at academic institutions
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] in the United Kingdom and United States. The main re-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] searcher has a background as a policy practitioner and re-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] searcher at the intersection of AI ethics, governance and re-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] sponsibility, while the two co-authors have academic back-
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] grounds researching AI policy and sociotechnical health
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] systems, respectively. These backgrounds impacted the
[2026-04-04 18:23:53] [stdout] framing and analysis of the qualitative study.
