[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] Gap from
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] Opacity
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] Hobbes : Does not incorporate requirements for institutional transparency.
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] Locke : Public justification principles undermined when decision-making is not
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] accessible to public understanding.
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] Rousseau : Co-authorship norms inapplicable where interpretability is absent.
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] Rawls : Public reason is limited when opacity obstructs reciprocal justification.
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] Nozick : Accepts non-transparency where no explicit rights violations are
[2026-04-04 18:26:00] [stdout] evident.
